title: Sharon Stone: The Beauty of Living Twice
text:
I've often thought Sharon Stone was an interesting person, interesting beyond her film career. The more I learn about her the more I am amazed. I really wish I'd met her.

Oddly, I just found out she wrote a book (and I call myself a fan ... HA).

It appears she's had a rough road in life.

I think this book is somewhat relevant to the hacker community. I know a few people who have had difficulties and find solace in solitary programming or gaming. It is easier to interact with machines than people. Her story might touch a few lives.

Rule by Strategy
text:
Hi,

I'm trying to find out if there has been any research into rule by strategy.

Now that we can encode a strategy into a computer it should be possible for us to explore strategic systems that are larger than one person's thoughts.

This could help us with some thorny problems like climate change and AI risk.

I'm using the definition of strategy from this video https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=iuYlGRnC7J8

Ask HN: New Midjourney API – Why are they using Discord?
text:
Hey everyone,

I recently built a tool called https://thenextleg.io that allows you to experiment and integrate Midjourney, the AI image generation software, into your workflow and automate your Midjourney interactions. I've noticed that Midjourney uses Discord as its interface, which is why I thought it'd be helpful to create an API for it.

I'm curious, has anyone else wondered why Midjourney uses Discord? Personally, I think it's an interesting choice, but it may not be for everyone. That being said, if you're interested in trying out a different way of interacting with Midjourney, feel free to check out https://thenextleg.io.

I also created a 1-minute YouTube video to demonstrate how to use the tool, which you can find here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nLC1xq_2yAM.

Let me know your thoughts on Midjourney and Discord, and if you have any questions or feedback about The Next Leg, please feel free to share!
